{
  "stem": "6878.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "On the railway station, they used to sell them at [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Tembo Beach ?].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I took talked in that farmer that his wife bought this on the railway station for [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Tembo ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So it was fine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And one day, being on the airport, I saw trucks-- railway trucks-- barbed with barbed wire, doors and windows with barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they stopped on the airport.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There must have been about 100 trucks, and that was in the middle of the day, something about 3:00 in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I saw it that-- and I thought that's definitely for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Because people were talking already that they're going to deport from the Jewish-- Jewish to Estonia, something like this.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So what I did is I took off my stars, and I escaped from work, and I went down-- to come to the ghetto, I had to come across two rivers by the name the Nemen and the Vilia.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went down and I find fishing boats.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were not locked.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I jumped into fishing boat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I sailed across the one river, and I walked a little island, the same that river.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I came to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I said, Ida-- my wife was Ida-- [GERMAN] Ida, I'm sure that the railway trucks, which I saw it now with barbed wire, must be for us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Just let's take out our little boy, and we already had to little arrangements with the police-- Jewish policeman.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He will help us to take out the little boy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when that same afternoon, when the mass of people came to the ghetto, that policeman, I had my wife-- my little boy I had under a raincoat, holding him under a raincoat with a sleeping tablet.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was asleep.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
